Not the raw recruit, marching from the bosom of his wife into the fever heat of his first battle; not the dead man's ghost encountering the first unknown phantom in the other world;--neither of these can feel stranger and stronger emotions than that man does, who for the first time finds himself pulling into the charmed, churned circle of the hunted sperm whale.  Swimming round it we picked up the floating oars, and lashing them across the gunwale, tumbled back to our places.  They were hidden down there. 

