All four boats were now in keen pursuit of that one spot of troubled water and air. 

Meanwhile Stubb, the third mate, betrayed no such far-gazing solicitudes.  Again we swam for it, were dashed against it by the seas, and were at last taken up and safely landed on board.  Meanwhile the driving scud, rack, and mist, grew darker with the shadows of night; no sign of the ship could be seen.  Less swart in aspect, the companions of this figure were of that vivid, tiger-yellow complexion peculiar to some of the aboriginal natives of the Manillas;--a race notorious for a certain diabolism of subtilty, and by some honest white mariners supposed to be the paid spies and secret confidential agents on the water of the devil, their lord, whose counting-room they suppose to be elsewhere.  So, so, so, then:--softly, softly! 

